t nazgul</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 828<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/13/03 11:27 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I quit EQ and it only gets better!!!</span><hr size=1> Heh, not everyone who says &quot;I'm leaving to get a life&quot; falls back into the vicious cycle of computer game addiction.  I left EQ about a year ago and my life has been much better off.  Right after the bailout I would play Ghost Recon a couple hours a day, but eventually games had less and less appeal and now I haven't played anything in days.<br>
<br>
What do I do with my spare time?  I finally setup a functional and useful Linux box (I had only toyed with Linux in the past).  I got a kickass new job.  I'm on track to get my CISSP certification.  Oh, and I'm finally reading books and learning again (an aspect of my life that EQ STOPPED COLD FOR YEARS).<br>
<br>
Have I ever missed EQ?  Maybe once or twice.  Then I remember my job and education and I don't regret it at all.<br>
<br>
