<br>
The next step is quitting these boards, though.  I waste as much time here as I did in EQ.  Although here I sometimes get a bit more of a sense of satisfaction and self-improvement than with EQ.  In the end, EQ just took too much time, committment, and energy to have any fun-- even with their new improvements or maybe even because of them.  If I was going to do something as boring as grinding XP, I may as well get paid for it.<br>
<br>
In some ways I really do regret ever picking up EQ in the first place.  I've definitely met some cool people and maintained some college relationships that would have otherwise fallen apart, but I started playing EQ to take my mind off of a girl that I was depressed about.  That was a really bad idea.  The relationship had been terribly one-sided had caused my grades to suffer, and EQ only made matters worse.  While due to monetary concerns I may not have been able to go to grad school anyway, and trying to finish two drastically different majors might not have been the brightest idea, I have almost no doubt that the results of my Music Theory GRE are because I played EQ while doing practice the tests.   Had I taken the test the year earlier, pre-EQ, I'm pretty sure I would have owned it.<br>
<br>
But really I try not to dwell on it.  Some people can handle EQ a lot better than I could, and I don't like to feel as if I'm judging someone. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=valtser>Valtser</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice... forever!</span><br>  Posts: 383<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/14/03 9:12 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I quit EQ and it only gets better!!!</span><hr size=1> Whoa! Goladus I do some of the same hobbies that you do. I work out, write music, and sing. But what really got me off EQ was that EQ was just starting to get gay. Till now when they added all of the cool features I feel like I want to go back. But i don't want to go through the installation again and patching so bleh.<br>
